The Recollection
Thou spark of life awake| 
In the faint glow of the forest;
The sun awakes, and
He wakes all that thou canst seek,
Though unseen in the deep, eternal game.
What light and joy can kindle things like you,
In the height of the melancholy moon?

- Percy Bysshe Shelley
